In a case reminiscent of David versus Goliath, impoverished residents of Ceres are being forced to choose between losing their indigent subsidies and accepting the installation of water management devices against their will.
This has resulted in the formation of a women-led organisation called the Fighting for Water Justice Coalition (FWJC) in this Western Cape town.
According to the FWJC, news started to make the rounds in 2016 that the Witzenberg Municipality was planning to install water management devices, but it did not happen then.
FWJC convenor Naomi Betana says a sad reality hit the nerve when they heard in a council meeting in 2018 that R2.7 million had been allocated for these devices.
<img data-attachment-id="20356" data-permalink="https://www.newframe.com/ceres-residents-fight-unnecessary-water-rationing/20jan_cereswater_bc-2/" data-orig-file="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/20Jan_CeresWater_BC-2-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="2560,1707" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;2&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Photographer: Barry Christianson&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;X-Pro2&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;23 November 2019:  Naomi Betana is one of the activists involved in organising resistance to the installation of water meters in the area. She is concerned that most people are not aware of the implications of having the water meter installed. Photographer: Barry Christianson.&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1574514022&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;Barry Christianson 2019&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;35&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;800&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.002&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="20Jan_CeresWater_BC-2" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/20Jan_CeresWater_BC-2-300x200.jpg" data-large-file="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/20Jan_CeresWater_BC-2-1024x683.jpg" src="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/20Jan_CeresWater_BC-2-scaled.jpg" alt="23 November 2019: Naomi Betina is one of the activists involved in organising resistance to the installation of water meters in the Ceres area. She is concerned that most people are not aware of the implications of having the device installed. " class="wp-image-20356" srcset="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/20Jan_CeresWater_BC-2-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/20Jan_CeresWater_BC-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/20Jan_CeresWater_BC-2-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://